Since the two if() statements above (FigureÂ 4 and FigureÂ 5) have mutually exclusive conditions (i.e., there are no situations where both can be TRUE), we can (and should) combine them into one if-else-if statement.Â  The following code is functionally the same but more efficient (i.e., faster):



for(i in 1:numDays)
{
  if(highTemps[i] &gt; 60 & noonCond[i] == "Sunny")
  {
    cat("day", i, " good day to go out\n");
  }else if(highTemps[i] &lt;= 50 & noonCond[i] == "Rain")
  {
    cat("day", i, " good day to stay in\n");
  }
}


